# Project Rules

## Language

- ALL code, comments, docstrings, variable names, function names, class names, and commit messages MUST be written in English.
- ALL documentation files (README, inline docs, API descriptions) MUST be written in English.
- Templates and bot message TEXT CONTENT (user-facing strings) may be in Russian or Uzbek when required by the product spec, but code surrounding them stays in English.
- The AI assistant communicates with the developer in Russian in chat, but everything committed to the repository must be in English.

## Code Style

- Follow PEP 8 for Python code.
- Use type hints on all function signatures.
- Use async/await consistently throughout the codebase — no blocking I/O in async functions.
- Prefer explicit over implicit.
- Use Pydantic models for all data validation.
- Keep functions small and single-purpose (SRP).

## Architecture Rules

- Services never import from handlers; handlers import from services.
- Database models live in `app/models/`. Business logic lives in `app/services/`. HTTP/Telegram handlers live in `app/bot/handlers/` and `app/admin/routes/`.
- Never put SQL queries directly in handlers — always go through a service.
- All settings are loaded via `app/core/config.py` (Pydantic Settings) for env vars, and via `app/services/settings_service.py` for DB-stored settings.

## Security

- Never log secrets (tokens, passwords, API keys).
- Always validate and sanitize file uploads.
- Use `secrets.compare_digest` for credential comparison.
